          "ins_item_num": null,
          "ins_total": null,
          "f9": "We are requesting 25.33 SQ for tear off, haul and dispose of laminated composition shingles for the main house roof.\n\nThe difference is $2,083.34. Per Xactimate pricing, the cost is $2,083.34 for this tear-off scope. This line item was not included in the insurance report but is necessary to complete the roofing repairs.\n\nThe existing laminated shingles must be completely removed before new roofing materials can be installed. This tear-off work includes safe removal of all existing shingles, proper disposal of materials, and hauling debris from the job site. The quantity of 25.33 SQ matches the roof area that requires shingle replacement as documented in our EagleView measurements.\n\nThis tear-off scope is a standard and necessary first step in the roofing repair process and is required to access the roof deck for proper inspection and to ensure the new roofing system can be installed according to manufacturer specifications and building code requirements.",
